  "text": "In this paper, the numerical schemes for solving [CITATION_1] are not included; one may refer to [CITATION_2] for more details. To summarize, by iteratively integrating (10) numerically, the level-set function φ(x, y, t) will eventually converge at a time, denoted by t e ; hence, we obtain the final level-set function φ e = φ(x, y, t e ). Many geometric quantities of detected cracks, such as perimeter (total length of closed boundary), area, curvature, and normal direction of crack boundaries, can be computed directly with φ e . However, we believe that the area, perimeter, and width are of primary engineering interest.",
